# Windows Event ID — Quick Reference

## Malware Execution
| Event ID | Log | What it means | What to look for |
|----------|-----|---------------|------------------|
| 4688 | Security | Process created | NewProcessName path, ParentProcessName, CommandLine args |
| 4689 | Security | Process exited | Pair with 4688 for runtime duration |
| 7045 | System | New service installed | ServiceName, ImagePath, AccountName |
| 4698 | Security | Scheduled task created | Task name, action path, trigger time |
| 4702 | Security | Scheduled task modified | Check what changed and who changed it |
| 7036 | System | Service started/stopped | Pair with 7045 |

## Logon & Lateral Movement
| Event ID | Log | What it means | What to look for |
|----------|-----|---------------|------------------|
| 4624 | Security | Successful logon | LogonType, IpAddress, unusual hours |
| 4625 | Security | Failed logon | Bursts = brute force |
| 4648 | Security | Logon with explicit credentials | Pass-the-hash indicator |
| 4778 | Security | RDP session reconnected | ClientAddress |
| 4779 | Security | RDP session disconnected | Pair with 4778 |
| 1149 | TermServices | RDP authentication | Fires before full logon |
| 4776 | Security | NTLM auth attempt | Pass-the-hash always uses NTLM |

## Logon Types
| Type | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| 2 | Interactive — keyboard at machine |
| 3 | Network — SMB / file share |
| 5 | Service logon |
| 10 | RDP |
| 11 | Cached credentials |

## Account & Privilege Changes
| Event ID | Log | What it means | What to look for |
|----------|-----|---------------|------------------|
| 4720 | Security | New user account created | Any unknown account = backdoor |
| 4732 | Security | User added to Administrators | 4720 + 4732 together = backdoor admin |
| 4672 | Security | Special privileges assigned | Unexpected accounts getting admin |
| 4724 | Security | Password reset attempted | Attacker locking out defenders |
| 4756 | Security | User added to security group | Which group? |

## Defense Evasion
| Event ID | Log | What it means | What to look for |
|----------|-----|---------------|------------------|
| 1102 | Security | Security log cleared — CRITICAL | Note timestamp, pivot to MFT/prefetch |
| 104 | System | System log cleared — CRITICAL | Same as above |
| 4719 | Security | Audit policy changed | Attacker disabling logging |
| 7040 | System | Service start type changed | AV/Defender disabled? |

## PowerShell
| Event ID | Log | What it means | What to look for |
|----------|-----|---------------|------------------|
| 4104 | PowerShell | Script block — full script captured | IEX, DownloadString, -EncodedCommand, Invoke-Mimikatz |
| 4103 | PowerShell | Pipeline execution | Each command in the pipeline |
| 400 | PowerShell | Engine started | HostApplication — how was PS invoked? |

## Sysmon (if installed)
| Event ID | Log | What it means | What to look for |
|----------|-----|---------------|------------------|
| 1 | Sysmon | Process create | Hash, full CLI, parent hash — richer than 4688 |
| 3 | Sysmon | Network connection | Which process, destination IP + port, C2 traffic |
| 11 | Sysmon | File created | Dropper activity — what process created what file |
| 13 | Sysmon | Registry value set | Run keys, persistence paths |
| 22 | Sysmon | DNS query | C2 domains, DGA patterns |

## Quick Cheatsheet
| Scenario | Event IDs to filter |
|----------|-------------------|
| Malware ran | 4688, 7045, 4698 |
| RDP access | 4624 Type 10, 1149 |
| Brute force | 4625 bursts then 4624 |
| Pass-the-hash | 4648 + Type 3 + 4776 |
| Backdoor account | 4720 + 4732 |
| Logs wiped | 1102, 104 |
| PowerShell attack | 4104 |
| Privilege escalation | 4672, 4732, 4756 |
